853df69c-a24a-4cce-86d7-cf2d0cf06496	students.geo_heatmap	show geographic heatmap of student home locations	student location heatmap student home areas map student distribution geo heatmap where do students live student addresses map student catchment area geographic distribution student origin areas student coordinates map density	["show me a heatmap of where my students live", "which areas do most students come from", "geographic distribution of students", "plot student home locations on a map", "student catchment area heatmap", "where are my students located", "show student address density map"]	TWO-STEP PROCESS ONLY:\nSTEP 1 — Fetch coordinates using dynamic_select_query:\n  - table: "students"\n  - projection: ["(address).latitude AS lat", "(address).longitude AS lon"]\n  - Add any filters via where clause (e.g. class_id, gender) if specified by user\n  - Drop rows where lat or lon is NULL before passing to next step\n\nSTEP 2 — Render heatmap using generate_geo_heatmap:\n  - Format fetched rows as CSV string with columns: lat, lon\n  - Set json_kwargs: {"zoom_start": 12, "radius": 20, "blur": 25, "title": "Student Home Locations", "tiles": "OpenStreetMap.Mapnik"}\n  - If user specifies a region/city, adjust zoom_start accordingly (city=12, district=10, state=7)\n  - NEVER pass NULL or empty coordinates to the heatmap tool\n\nExecution Rules:\n  - NEVER generate raw SQL with JOINs or manual coordinate math\n  - ALWAYS use dynamic_select_query for data fetching\n  - ALWAYS use generate_geo_heatmap for rendering — never render maps inline\n  - If zero valid coordinates returned, inform user and stop	[{"args": {"limit": 1000, "table": "students", "where": "$OPTIONAL_FILTERS", "projection": ["(address).latitude AS lat", "(address).longitude AS lon"]}, "step": 1, "tool": "dynamic_select_query"}, {"args": {"csv_data": "$CSV_FROM_STEP1", "json_kwargs": "{\\"zoom_start\\": 12, \\"radius\\": 20, \\"blur\\": 25, \\"title\\": \\"Student Home Locations\\", \\"tiles\\": \\"